<subSubSection pageNumber="685" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="685">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="685">Note:</emphasis>
Andersson (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="685">Nordic J. Bot.</emphasis>
1: 769. 1981) gave an extensive review of the history of this name. The cited Plumier element leads to a generic illustration (t. 3) for 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="685">Bihai</emphasis>
which included what Plumier regarded as three different species, so the plate cannot be treated as original material for 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="685">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Heliconiaceae" genus="Musa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bihai">M. bihai</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Andersson therefore designated a later Dahlberg collection (286.1 LINN) as a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
, but Maas &amp; De Rooij had previously treated the same collection as the type (accepted as a neotypification under Art. 9.8).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
